President Barack Obama congratulates the Afghan people on the start of their official election campaign period. He emphasizes the importance of accountability, transparency, and reintegration of fighters who are ready for peace. He also highlights the need for Afghanistan to work with its neighboring countries to promote security and opportunity in the region. The United States does not support or oppose any particular candidate but supports the right of the Afghan people to choose their own leaders. The United States is working with Afghan electoral authorities and the United Nations to ensure a credible and inclusive election process. The goal is to establish an enduring partnership with the Afghan people, focusing on governance, security, justice, and economic opportunity for all Afghans.